  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 29 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 850 mg
author: HelloFresh
time required: 20 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/moo-shu-chicken-bowls-66b39a2d995e511e4eca9aea
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Thinly slice @Scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Quarter @Lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Chopped Chicken Breast{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir scallion whites and @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce} into pan with chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, until just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Hoisin Sauce{2%tablespoon}, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, @Sweet Soy Glaze{2 1/2%tablespoon}, and @Sugar{1/2%teaspoon} until thoroughly combined. Turn off heat.

> We sent more sweet soy glaze - save the remaining for later servings.

Taste and season with juice from half the lime, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with moo shu chicken. Sprinkle with scallion greens and as many @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon} as you like. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°. Swap in beef for chicken if preferred.